Productivity in the United States grew at an increasing rate throughout the 19th century and was most rapid in the early to middle decades of the 20th century.[37][38][39][40][41] U.S. productivity growth spiked towards the end of the century in 1996–2004, due to an acceleration in the rate of technological innovation known as Moore's law.[42][43][44][45] After 2004 U.S. productivity growth returned to the low levels of 1972–96.[42]
